&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Full or part-time hours 1 year fixed to cover Maternity leave.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking for highly motivated, dynamic and forward thinking experienced nurses with excellent clinical and interpersonal skills to join our friendly team providing a high standard of care. Your role will be varied, working with specialities, where you can demonstrate your clinical practise and further enhance your knowledge and skills.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Experience as a registered nurse in an acute trust is essential. You will have the opportunity to utilise your phlebotomy and wound care skills, and we will train you to assist with a variety of procedures that are carried out in clinic such as minor operations.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will need to be enthusiastic, be able to use your own initiative, and have well developed time-management and communication skills.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post will also involve providing mentoring and supporting junior and new staff to the department.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will need to have the flexibility to work a variable shift pattern between 0800- 1830 including weekends to provide a 7 day service across Frimley Health South Outpatients which includes Frimley Park Hospital, Aldershot Centre for Health and Fleet Community Hospital as required.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You can enjoy:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;· A full induction programme&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;· A competency based appraisal system&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;· Opportunities to undertake formal study&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
